# ============================================================
#  Cortex Protocol — CODEOWNERS
#  Critical file protection: mandatory Protocol Steward review
# ============================================================
#
#  CODEOWNERS enforces that certain files cannot be merged
#  via Pull Request without explicit approval from the designated
#  owner — even if all CI checks pass.
#
#  HOW IT WORKS:
#  When a PR modifies a file matching a pattern below, GitHub
#  automatically adds the listed owner as a required reviewer.
#  The PR cannot be merged until that reviewer approves.
#
#  SETUP REQUIRED (one-time):
#  In repo Settings → Branches → main branch protection:
#  ✅ Require a pull request before merging
#  ✅ Require approvals: 1
#  ✅ Require review from Code Owners
#  ✅ Dismiss stale pull request approvals when new commits are pushed
#  ✅ Require status checks to pass before merging
#     → ci / test-suite (ubuntu-24.04, 3.10)
#     → ci / test-suite (ubuntu-24.04, 3.11)
#     → ci / test-suite (ubuntu-24.04, 3.12)
#     → ci / bandit-sast
#     → ci / dependency-audit
#     → ci / crypto-regression
#     → sal-boundary-guard / SAL Boundary — Invariant Check
#  ✅ Require branches to be up to date before merging
#  ✅ Do not allow bypassing the above settings
#
#  OWNER NOTATION:
#  Replace @cortex-psylead with the actual GitHub username(s)
#  of the Protocol Steward account(s).

# ── Default owner for everything not explicitly listed ──────────
*                               @cortex-psylead

# ── SAL — Core sovereignty layer ────────────────────────────────
# Any change to the SAL requires Protocol Steward review.
# This is the most critical boundary in the protocol.
/src/sal/                       @cortex-psylead
/src/ethos/                     @cortex-psylead
/src/keros/                     @cortex-psylead
/src/limes/                     @cortex-psylead
/src/governance/                @cortex-psylead

# ── Layer 1 — Bare metal firmware specification ──────────────────
# Any change to C/Rust/ASM firmware requires Protocol Steward
# AND will require White Branch review before merge.
/src/layer1/                    @cortex-psylead

# ── Layer 2 — ZKP circuits ──────────────────────────────────────
/src/layer2/                    @cortex-psylead

# ── CI/CD — Workflow files ───────────────────────────────────────
# Changes to CI could bypass security checks.
# Only the Protocol Steward can modify them.
/.github/                       @cortex-psylead

# ── Governance and legal documents ──────────────────────────────
# These documents are the Digital Constitution of the project.
# No external contributor may modify them unilaterally.
/docs/governance/               @cortex-psylead
/docs/legal/                    @cortex-psylead
SECURITY.md                     @cortex-psylead
CONTRIBUTING.md                 @cortex-psylead

# ── Dependency manifest ──────────────────────────────────────────
# requirements.txt changes affect the entire cryptographic stack.
requirements.txt                @cortex-psylead

# ── Test suite ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tests define what "correct behavior" means for the protocol.
/tests/                         @cortex-psylead

# ── Clinical documents ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Require White Branch co-review (add White Branch GitHub handles
# when Governance Nodes are constituted in Milestone 1)
/docs/clinical/                 @cortex-psylead
# Future: /docs/clinical/     @cortex-psylead @white-branch-node-1
